sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    
    actor User
    participant Browser as Browser (Next.js)
    participant NextCache as Next.js Server (TanStack/Proxy)
    participant APIGateway as FastAPI (Router)
    participant RAGSvc as RAG Orchestrator (Service)
    participant VDB as Pinecone (Vector Store)
    participant LLM as OpenAI (text-emb & gpt-4o)
    participant Avatar as HeyGen (Avatar API)

    User->>Browser: Types query & submits
    Browser->>NextCache: POST /api/chat {query, session}
    NextCache->>APIGateway: Proxy POST /v1/chat + TraceID
    
    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over APIGateway, RAGSvc: Clean Architecture Boundary
        APIGateway->>RAGSvc: Call `answer_query(query)`
        
        Note over RAGSvc, LLM: 1. Vectorization
        RAGSvc->>LLM: `create_embedding("text-embedding-3-large", query)`
        LLM-->>RAGSvc: Returns [Vector]
        
        Note over RAGSvc, VDB: 2. Semantic Search
        RAGSvc->>VDB: `query(vector, top_k=5)`
        VDB-->>RAGSvc: Returns chunks + BookStack IDs + Scores
        
        Note over RAGSvc: 3. Confidence Threshold Check
        alt Score < Minimum Threshold
            RAGSvc-->>APIGateway: raise ErrNoContextFound()
            APIGateway-->>NextCache: 404/422 with Domain Error RFC 7807
            NextCache-->>Browser: Trigger Graceful Decline UI
        else Score >= Minimum Threshold
            Note over RAGSvc, LLM: 4. Generation
            RAGSvc->>LLM: `stream("gpt-4o", prompt + context chunks)`
            LLM-->>RAGSvc: Stream tokens
            RAGSvc-->>APIGateway: Yield generator (Stream Response)
        end
    end
    
    rect rgb(253, 245, 230)
        Note over RAGSvc, Avatar: 5. Avatar Trigger (Async/Background)
        %% Assuming Avatar is triggered post-LLM or via dual-stream 
        RAGSvc->>Avatar: POST `/v1/avatar/speak` {text_chunk}
        Avatar-->>Browser: WebRTC stream updates directly
    end

    APIGateway-->>NextCache: Stream chunk + BookStack IDs (Attribution)
    NextCache-->>Browser: Update UI (Markdown Chat + Source Links)
    Browser-->>User: Views generated answer & sources
